Untangled is a tool that helps journalists investigate and report on complex networks. It does this by providing a way to collect, analyze, and visualize data about relationships between people, organizations, and other entities.

Untangled can be used to investigate a wide range of topics, including political corruption, financial crime, and organized crime. It can also be used to track the spread of information and ideas online.

Untangled is a powerful tool that can help journalists uncover hidden stories and hold powerful people accountable. However, it is important to note that Untangled is not a magic bullet. It requires careful planning and execution to use effectively.

If you are interested in learning more about Untangled, please visit the Knight Lab website.
